<paragraph blockId="22.[136,1452,373,508]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,410,436]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Notes:—</emphasis>
This Bolivian endemic may produce up to 
<quantity box="[787,832,410,436]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
proliferous plants,. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Schlechter" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1234,1339,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutex">
<emphasis box="[1234,1339,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">M. frutex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is also found in 
<collectingCountry box="[290,376,446,472]" name="Bolivia" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. However, it is distinguished from the latter by its whitish flowers and acute lateral lip lobes 
<emphasis box="[1421,1444,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. yellowish to brownish flowers and lip margins obscurely angled.
</paragraph>
